And I was moved by the resilience and power of women around the world as they stand up for human rights. I feel very fortunate to be living the life that I have. There is no way you can read a book like "Half the Sky", learn about the oppression and inequalities that still exist in this "modern" world, and not be moved to action. This money can be used to send their children to school, pay for hospital visits, and improve lives in general.
